The girl of my dreams 
Comes from a rainforest 
Mixed in a bag 
Of loose tea 

Her honey colored hair 
Makes the boiling water sweet 
Hibiscus colored lips 
With a gentle hint of açaí 

I’ll steep her in my teacup 
For as long as she needs 
And I’ll drink every last drop 
With sugar
With cream

But to me there’s meaning seldom heard.
For everything I am today,

For enriching my life in so many ways.
She set me straight and then set me free,
And that’s what the word "mother" means to me.

— Karl Fuchs

“Sleep late, have fun, get wild, drink whiskey.” – Hunter S. Thompson

Peanut Butter Manhattan

•2 oz Elijah Craig Rye Whiskey <peanut butter fat-washed>
•3/4 oz Sweet Vermouth
•2 Dashes Mole Bitters
•Orange Zest
•Garnish - Gold Adorned 
Peanut Butter Spheres 

🥜 Peanut Butter Fat-Washed Rye: Spread peanut butter (one pound of peanut butter for every liter of Whiskey ) across the bottom of a pan. Pour Rye on top of the peanut butter. Cover and let sit for 2 days.
Strain with a cheese cloth until all the liquid is out. Pour it back into the bottle for use. Drink responsibly.

The symbolism behind dragon fruit is very meaningful. In the East, dragons are intended to represent vitality, power and luck.

Are you familiar with the Myth? 

The Dragon fruit was created thousands of years ago by fire breathing dragons. During a battle when the dragon would breathe fire the last thing to come out would be the fruit. After the dragon is slain the fruit is collected and presented to the Emperor as a coveted treasure and indication of victory.

Drop your thoughts in the comments. Cheers!

Cocktail & Photography by: @melis_boozy_cure 📸

Dragon Fruit Cosmopolitan 
1 1/2 oz Vodka 
1 oz Fresh Watermelon Juice
1/2 oz Bauchant Orange Liq
1/2 oz Red Pitaya Dragon Fruit Syrup
1/2 oz Lime Juice
Garnish~🐉 Fruit

Nothing Gold Can Stay✨

Nature’s first green is gold,
Her hardest hue to hold.
Her early leaf’s a flower;
But only so an hour.
Then leaf subsides to leaf.
So Eden sank to grief,
So dawn goes down to day.
Nothing gold can stay…
—S. E. Hinton
